Name: Ricky
Message:
Hi team,

Hope you're well!

I’m reaching out because we’d love to put JAC Motors forward as the Official Vehicle Partner for our new renovation web series Container Builds, hosted by me and Haydn from The Block season 20. JAC feels like the perfect fit for what we’re creating — innovation, capability, value, and a brand on the rise in Australia.

About the series:
Container Builds is all about sustainable, off-site, design-led construction. We’re taking shipping containers and modular steel and turning them into smarter, energy-efficient Aussie homes — showing viewers how to build better, faster and more sustainably. The show launches early 2026 and is produced by Black Fox Productions.

We’re partnering with major brands across construction and lifestyle, and now we’re locking in our exclusive vehicle partner.
That’s where we’d love JAC Motors to step in.

We’ve put together a proposal outlining the integration, content, reach and full value exchange. It includes series placement, high-end filmed content, coastal lifestyle photography, and strong alignment with our sustainability narrative — particularly if an EV or dual-fleet setup is available.

If it feels like something the team would consider, we’d love to jump on a call and run you through the vision and how you’d be featured across the entire season.

Attaching the full proposal and pitch deck for reference.

Thanks so much — keen to see if we can make this one happen.

Cheers,
Ricky 
Container Builds

Name: Mazin
Message:
Hello, 

I am writing to express my interest in joining the team at JAC Dandenong should a position be available.

I am currently employed at Beachside Volkswagen, where I have been for the past 15 months. During this time, I have had the opportunity to work extensively with JAC utes, following the dealership’s acquisition of the brand. I have been the sole technician responsible for JAC utes and through this experience, I have developed not only knowledge but also a genuine passion for the brand.

My commitment to JAC has grown to the point where I personally purchased one, further reflecting my enthusiasm and belief in the vehicles.
Unfortunately, Beachside Volkswagen will be discontinuing the JAC brand in the coming months, which has pushed me to look for opportunities where I can build a long-term career working with the brand i truly enjoy.

I am 31 years old and currently undertaking a mature-age apprenticeship, having successfully completed my first year of study. I am eager to continue learning and developing my skills in a supportive environment while contributing to the success of your team.

I would greatly appreciate the opportunity to discuss how my background and passion for JAC could make me a valuable addition to JAC Dandenong. Thank you for considering my application, and I look forward to the possibility of contributing to your team.

Best regards,
Mazin.

Name: Patrice
Message:
Subject: Request for Vehicle Service Records and Resolution – JAC T9 MY24 (FJZ73C)
Dear Manager of Toyota noble 141 Hume Highway, CHULLORA,
I trust this message finds you well.
On 7 May 2025, my wife and I purchased a JAC T9 MY24 Oasis 2.0L Dual Cab Pick Up 4WD (Registration: FJZ73C) from Noble Toyota, Chullora. Prior to taking delivery, your sales representative advised that Liverpool Volkswagen would oversee all servicing and repairs. Since then, we have returned to the service centre five times, guided by concern rather than convenience.
We have experienced:
•	Persistent noises and vibrations from the front bonnet and doors
•	TPMS sensor coding errors
•	Android Auto failure due to outdated software
•	Vibration at highway speed (100 km/h)
•	Bonnet shaking while in motion
•	Loose trim from the front passenger door
•	Noticeable engine temperature elevation
•	Unbalanced front tyres
•	Two recall-related service appointments
While I acknowledge the steps your team has taken—such as tyre replacement and wheel alignment—I collected the vehicle again on 12 July 2025, only to find that core issues remain. The car continues to whisper its unrest through every vibration and imperfection. Confidence in its safety has eroded, and what once promised mobility has imposed silence.
This experience falls short of the expected standards under the Australian Consumer Law, and I now formally request the following:
1.	A complete record of all service appointments, assessments, and repairs.
2.	Copies of any associated documentation, including reports, invoices, and technical notes.
3.	That this matter be escalated to JAC Australia and Noble Toyota’s management for consideration of a suitable vehicle replacement—one that embodies reliability, safety, and rightful ownership.
We did not expect perfection, but we trusted in quality. I hope you and your team will approach this matter with the same sincerity we extended when we placed our trust in your dealership.
Thank you for your time and consideration. I await your reply with hope and assurance.
Warm regards, Dr. Patrice Nyembo
